				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\mathrm{H}}_3\mathrm{C}-\mathrm{CH}=\mathrm{C}{\mathrm{H}}_2+\mathrm{CO}\leftrightarrow {\mathrm{H}}_3\mathrm{C}-\mathrm{CH}=\mathrm{C}\mathrm{H}-\mathrm{HC}=\mathrm{O}\ {\Delta }_{\mathrm{R}}{\mathrm{H}}^{\mathrm{o}}=-18.9\ \mathrm{kJ}/\mathrm{mol} $$\end{document}

The formed croton aldehyde is subsequently hydrogenated to butanol according to:
